        <name>GetDegrees</name>
        <qualifiedname>Dali::Orientation::GetDegrees</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Returns the orientation of the device in degrees. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This is one of four discrete values, in degrees clockwise: 0, 90, 180, &amp; 270 For a device with a portrait form-factor: 0 indicates that the device is in the &quot;normal&quot; portrait orientation. 90 indicates that device has been rotated clockwise, into a landscape orientation. <simplesect kind="return"><para>The orientation in degrees clockwise. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
